question: 親子丼
sourceMnemonic: This very common food is <kanji>parent</kanji> and <kanji>child</kanji> <kanji>rice bowl</kanji>, aka a <vocabulary>parent and child rice bowl</vocabulary>. The parent is a chicken. The child is an egg. This can also be called <vocabulary>chicken and egg rice bowl</vocabulary>, or simply <vocabulary>oyako-don</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: The reading is <ja>親</ja> and <ja>子</ja> and <ja>丼</ja> combined together.
